opinions.text:
ORDER
The petition for writ of certiorari is denied. Pursuant to § 28-35-32, counsel for the respondent is awarded a fee of $437.50 for his services performed in opposing the petition.

attorneys: Arlene Violet, Atty. Gen., Madis T. Su-varis, Sp. Asst. Atty. Gen., for petitioner.
Stephen N. Rappoport, Slepkow Slepkow & Rappoport, East Providence, for respondent.
casebody.head_matter:
STATE v. Doreen JACKSON.
No. 85-242-M.P.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
June 6, 1985.
Arlene Violet, Atty. Gen., Madis T. Su-varis, Sp. Asst. Atty. Gen., for petitioner.
Stephen N. Rappoport, Slepkow Slepkow & Rappoport, East Providence, for respondent.
